4
00:03:47,318 --> 00:03:49,966
<i>Know where your teammates are!</i>

5
00:03:51,034 --> 00:03:52,932
<i>All right, hold up. Hold it up.</i>

6
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:57,029
<i>New ball.
We are going to play with this ball.</i>

7
00:03:57,030 --> 00:03:59,141
<i>Invisible.</i>

8
00:04:02,616 --> 00:04:04,768
<i>It's funny. You think it's silly.</i>

9
00:04:04,769 --> 00:04:06,797
<i>Practice is the place
it's okay to feel silly.</i>

10
00:04:06,798 --> 00:04:07,986
<i>The practice floor.</i>

11
00:04:07,986 --> 00:04:10,517
<i>Not with people watching you play.</i>

12
00:04:10,518 --> 00:04:12,736
<i>Alright, you guys.
Run a couple plays.</i>

13
00:04:12,737 --> 00:04:13,842
<i>Set it up. Three game.</i>

14
00:04:13,843 --> 00:04:15,350
<i>Where's the ball?</i>

15
00:04:15,384 --> 00:04:17,644
<i>- In my mind, coach.
- It is in your mind.</i>

16
00:04:17,645 --> 00:04:21,148
<i>One brain! There you go!
That's the way to move it!</i>

17
00:04:21,149 --> 00:04:23,814
<i>You play better with the
invisible than the real ball.</i>

18
00:04:32,371 --> 00:04:34,174
<i>-Hey, kiddo.
-Hey, how are you?</i>

19
00:04:34,175 --> 00:04:35,182
<i>Good, how are you?</i>

20
00:04:35,183 --> 00:04:38,881
<i>You spas.
Yeah, I was there all alone.</i>

21
00:04:38,882 --> 00:04:39,895
<i>-Hi.
-Hey.</i>

22
00:04:41,692 --> 00:04:43,260
<i>You're late.</i>

23
00:04:44,387 --> 00:04:45,476
<i>Practice ran long.</i>

24
00:04:46,999 --> 00:04:50,232
<i>Oh, uh, Clyde, shoes, please?</i>

25
00:04:57,892 --> 00:04:59,521
<i>What is this?</i>

26
00:04:59,522 --> 00:05:02,604
<i>I needed work space for the business.
We're up and running.</i>

27
00:05:02,605 --> 00:05:04,542
<i>Hmm.</i>

28
00:05:05,395 --> 00:05:06,879
<i>Yeah.</i>

29
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:10,894
<i>The jewellery design. I told
you I was getting back into it.</i>

30
00:05:15,138 --> 00:05:17,010
<i>Stephanie, I had a bunch of stuff in here.</i>

31
00:05:17,011 --> 00:05:19,838
<i>I boxed up your stuff.
Your name's on it.</i>

32
00:05:19,839 --> 00:05:21,775
<i>Everything's in the closet.</i>

33
00:05:21,775 --> 00:05:26,256
<i>Don't you think I should
have packed up my office?</i>

34
00:05:26,257 --> 00:05:28,354
<i>It's not your office anymore.</i>

35
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:43,582
<i>Hey, kiddo. You ready to go?</i>

36
00:05:46,231 --> 00:05:47,891
<i>Which one you think is a better slogan?</i>

37
00:05:47,892 --> 00:05:50,114
<i>"Stop The Killing, Eat Vegetables...</i>

38
00:05:50,115 --> 00:05:52,168
<i>...or When You Eat Animals,
You Become One?</i>

39
00:05:54,167 --> 00:05:55,897
<i>First of all, that is awesome...</i>

40
00:05:55,898 --> 00:05:59,300
<i>...but Stop The Killing
is super catchy.</i>

41
00:05:59,301 --> 00:06:01,923
<i>-Get my message?
-Loud and clear.</i>

42
00:06:01,924 --> 00:06:05,266
<i>Miss Shandy said that if we get
200 signatures on our petition...</i>

43
00:06:05,267 --> 00:06:06,644
<i>...she will
take it to the principal...</i>

44
00:06:06,645 --> 00:06:09,457
<i>...and they'll consider
meat-free Mondays.</i>

45
00:06:09,458 --> 00:06:11,981
<i>Wow, that will make you so popular.</i>

46
00:06:11,982 --> 00:06:15,921
<i>Dad, were all one big
family on this planet...</i>

47
00:06:15,922 --> 00:06:17,051
<i>...no matter what species...</i>

48
00:06:17,052 --> 00:06:19,178
<i>...and we don't eat family, do we?</i>

49
00:06:19,179 --> 00:06:20,791
<i>No, we certainly do not.</i>

50
00:06:23,124 --> 00:06:24,420
<i>-Hi, Clyde.
-Hey.</i>

51
00:06:24,421 --> 00:06:28,080
<i>Careful. You are entering
a shoe-free zone.</i>

52
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:30,652
<i>I know. I got that
sign for Stephanie.</i>

53
00:06:30,653 --> 00:06:33,887
<i>You wouldn't believe
what's dragged indoors.</i>

54
00:06:33,888 --> 00:06:34,849
<i>I'm sure I wouldn't.</i>

55
00:06:34,850 --> 00:06:36,891
<i>-Hey!
-Hi.</i>

56
00:06:36,892 --> 00:06:38,426
<i>What are you up to tonight?</i>

57
00:06:38,427 --> 00:06:40,962
<i>-Going to a concert.
-Nice.</i>

58
00:06:40,963 --> 00:06:42,946
<i>Season tickets. Wagner.</i>

59
00:06:42,947 --> 00:06:47,144
<i>Wagner? Stephanie loves Wagner,
don't you, dear?</i>

60
00:06:47,145 --> 00:06:49,940
<i>I'll have them back Sunday after lunch.</i>

61
00:06:49,941 --> 00:06:50,798
<i>Okay.</i>

62
00:06:52,083 --> 00:06:57,017
<i>Em's still vegetarian, so keep an eye
on her, and her allergies, please.</i>

63
00:06:57,018 --> 00:06:58,577
<i>Last time she got hives.</i>

64
00:06:58,578 --> 00:07:01,660
<i>And healthy food,
stuff that grows on trees.</i>

65
00:07:01,660 --> 00:07:04,185
<i>No pizza, please. I mean it.</i>

66
00:07:04,186 --> 00:07:04,957
<i>You done?</i>

67
00:07:04,958 --> 00:07:06,335
<i>Yes.</i>

68
00:07:06,336 --> 00:07:08,438
<i>-Stephanie...
-Yes?</i>

69
00:07:08,439 --> 00:07:10,404
<i>I think I got this.</i>

70
00:07:10,405 --> 00:07:11,657
<i>-Okay.
-Okay.</i>

71
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:17,553
<i>-Bye, you guys! I love you!
-Bye!</i>

72
00:07:20,504 --> 00:07:25,002
<i>-Brett says I have an overbite.
-Give me a break, your teeth are fine.</i>

73
00:07:25,003 --> 00:07:28,521
<i>Brett's job is to tell
people they have bad teeth.</i>

74
00:07:28,522 --> 00:07:29,581
<i>That's how he makes money.</i>

75
00:07:29,582 --> 00:07:32,043
<i>He said he'd fix it for free.</i>

76
00:07:32,044 --> 00:07:34,263
<i>Uh, Dad?</i>

77
00:07:34,264 --> 00:07:35,801
<i>Yeah?</i>

78
00:07:35,802 --> 00:07:38,109
<i>You passed your apartment.</i>

79
00:07:38,110 --> 00:07:40,172
<i>Oh, I did, didn't I?</i>

80
00:07:40,173 --> 00:07:41,337
<i>Ta-dah!</i>

81
00:07:41,338 --> 00:07:42,492
<i>What is it?</i>

82
00:07:42,492 --> 00:07:45,045
<i>What is it? This is our new house.</i>

83
00:07:45,046 --> 00:07:47,633
<i>-It's in the middle of nowhere.
-Isn't it awesome?</i>

84
00:07:47,634 --> 00:07:49,911
<i>And critters come by from the woods.</i>

85
00:07:49,912 --> 00:07:52,363
<i>Yesterday, two raccoons on our porch.</i>

86
00:07:52,364 --> 00:07:53,172
<i>Really?</i>

87
00:07:53,173 --> 00:07:55,615
<i>Come on, Mopey McGee.</i>

88
00:07:56,568 --> 00:08:00,922
<i>Wow, this is pretty cool.</i>

89
00:08:00,923 --> 00:08:03,336
<i>Right? Bedrooms are upstairs.</i>

90
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:13,613
<i>I call the room facing the woods!</i>

91
00:08:13,614 --> 00:08:15,798
<i>You got it. That's your room.</i>

92
00:08:15,799 --> 00:08:17,800
<i>Dad, there's a doggie door!</i>

93
00:08:19,526 --> 00:08:22,059
<i>Lets get a dog from
the shelter. Please.</i>

94
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:24,918
<i>Please, please, please, please.</i>

95
00:08:24,918 --> 00:08:27,720
<i>You've got to be kidding me.
This does not work on me anymore.</i>

96
00:08:27,721 --> 00:08:30,472
<i>Daddy, yes, it does. Please.</i>

97
00:08:33,582 --> 00:08:34,555
<i>Cheers.</i>

98
00:08:34,556 --> 00:08:36,653
<i>-Cheers.
-Cheers.</i>

99
00:08:39,524 --> 00:08:41,455
<i>I think Mom would
really like this house.</i>

100
00:08:41,456 --> 00:08:42,874
<i>We should invite her for breakfast.</i>

101
00:08:42,875 --> 00:08:47,737
<i>Mom and Dad officially
divorced three months ago.</i>

102
00:08:47,738 --> 00:08:49,596
<i>Mom's not coming for pancakes.</i>

103
00:08:49,597 --> 00:08:51,618
<i>-That's enough.
-Its getting old.</i>

104
00:08:51,619 --> 00:08:54,394
<i>She thinks you're
getting back together.</i>

105
00:08:54,395 --> 00:08:59,571
<i>Em, your mom and I,
we just sort of, uh...</i>

106
00:08:59,572 --> 00:09:02,463
<i>...we forgot how to get along.</i>

107
00:09:02,464 --> 00:09:05,684
<i>And you both are moving on with your lives.</i>

108
00:09:05,685 --> 00:09:09,137
<i>I know. That's what Mom always says.</i>

109
00:09:10,034 --> 00:09:11,888
<i>Your mom says that?</i>

110
00:09:14,363 --> 00:09:18,195
<i>Okay. Then, there you have it.
You know, it’s for the best.</i>

111
00:09:18,196 --> 00:09:22,786
<i>Okay? So let's have our dinner.</i>

112
00:09:22,787 --> 00:09:24,878
<i>I'm not hungry anymore.</i>

113
00:09:26,544 --> 00:09:28,130
<i>Alright, clear your plate.</i>

114
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:37,265
<i>Hannah...</i>

115
00:09:37,266 --> 00:09:40,508
<i>You can't say that. It upsets your sister.</i>

116
00:09:41,524 --> 00:09:45,775
<i>For real?
You're going to blame this on me?</i>

117
00:09:45,776 --> 00:09:48,369
<i>Nice, Dad.</i>

118
00:09:52,737 --> 00:09:56,657
<i>"Walk a little faster,"
said the whiting to the snail.</i>

119
00:09:56,658 --> 00:10:01,004
<i>"There's a porpoise close behind us,
and he's treading on my tail."</i>

120
00:10:01,004 --> 00:10:02,543
<i>How was your day today?</i>

121
00:10:02,544 --> 00:10:05,384
<i>Okay. How was yours?</i>

122
00:10:05,385 --> 00:10:06,816
<i>Dinner was a failure.</i>

123
00:10:06,817 --> 00:10:09,848
<i>Make sure Mom doesn't
find out about dinner.</i>

124
00:10:09,849 --> 00:10:12,771
<i>She'll be mad pizza
doesn't grow on trees.</i>

125
00:10:12,772 --> 00:10:15,202
<i>I'll give you $5 if
you don't tell your mother.</i>

126
00:10:15,203 --> 00:10:18,235
<i>Make it 35 and we have a deal.</i>

127
00:10:21,916 --> 00:10:23,292
<i>Go to sleep.</i>

128
00:10:24,599 --> 00:10:25,841
<i>Leave the door open.</i>

129
00:10:25,842 --> 00:10:28,132
<i>What's the matter? You scared?</i>

130
00:10:28,133 --> 00:10:31,937
<i>No. Just... I want it open, okay?</i>

131
00:10:42,455 --> 00:10:44,828
<i>Dad, you need dishes.</i>

132
00:10:46,141 --> 00:10:47,635
<i>Okay.</i>

133
00:10:47,636 --> 00:10:50,241
<i>Hey, Clyde, its Trevor down at NC.</i>

134
00:10:50,242 --> 00:10:52,890
<i>Call me. I want to talk to you.</i>

135
00:10:52,891 --> 00:10:54,039
<i>Hope you're good, pal.</i>

136
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:56,377
<i>Dad, look! I'm a lady.</i>

137
00:11:20,316 --> 00:11:21,836
<i>Cool.</i>

138
00:11:37,445 --> 00:11:39,848
<i>-Daddy, can I get this?
-That is a lovely hat.</i>

139
00:11:39,849 --> 00:11:42,028
<i>Whatever you want, kiddo.</i>

140
00:11:42,029 --> 00:11:44,934
<i>So we found a couple things.
What's the damage?</i>

141
00:11:46,165 --> 00:11:49,339
<i>-How about 55?
-55.</i>

142
00:11:52,392 --> 00:11:55,238
<i>My daughters cleaned me out.
I have $48.</i>

143
00:11:55,239 --> 00:11:56,815
<i>-We'll put something back.
-Oh, no.</i>

144
00:11:56,816 --> 00:11:58,814
<i>-You sure?
-Yeah.</i>

145
00:11:58,815 --> 00:12:00,359
<i>-Thank you.
-Thank you.</i>

146
00:12:01,891 --> 00:12:05,017
<i>You're clearing out.
You moving or something?</i>

147
00:12:05,018 --> 00:12:08,642
<i>-No. Some of bills came up.
-Oh.</i>

148
00:12:41,615 --> 00:12:48,036
<i>No! No!</i>

149
00:12:59,354 --> 00:13:03,671
<i>Look at these carvings.
They're so pretty.</i>

150
00:13:05,462 --> 00:13:07,586
<i>These directions are ridiculous.</i>

151
00:13:07,587 --> 00:13:11,378
<i>Em, do me a favour and hand
me the screwdriver, please?</i>

152
00:13:12,266 --> 00:13:14,854
<i>But Daddy,
you said you'd get this open.</i>

153
00:13:17,462 --> 00:13:19,595
<i>Well, that's weird.
There aren't any seams.</i>

154
00:13:20,451 --> 00:13:21,910
<i>What does that mean?</i>

155
00:13:21,911 --> 00:13:26,361
<i>It means whoever made this
didn't want anybody to open it...</i>

156
00:13:26,362 --> 00:13:29,359
<i>...or they didn't want
anybody to open it easily.</i>

157
00:13:31,103 --> 00:13:34,662
<i>You hear that?
There's something in there.</i>

158
00:13:34,663 --> 00:13:39,351
<i>So somebody had to open it,
once upon a time.</i>

159
00:13:39,352 --> 00:13:41,619
<i>That is absolutely correct.</i>

160
00:13:44,037 --> 00:13:46,815
<i>-Daddy, no.
-I have to take it.</i>

161
00:13:46,816 --> 00:13:49,734
<i>-Trevor. Sorry, I missed your calls.
-Daddy.</i>

162
00:13:49,735 --> 00:13:50,630
<i>How's my old friend doing?</i>

163
00:13:50,631 --> 00:13:51,591
<i>Good.</i>

164
00:13:51,307 --> 00:13:52,318
<i>Daddy--</i>

165
00:13:52,319 --> 00:13:54,230
<i>You run a good program up there.</i>

166
00:13:54,231 --> 00:13:56,307
<i>You have two conference titles.</i>

167
00:13:56,308 --> 00:13:58,194
<i>You calling just to chat?</i>

168
00:13:58,195 --> 00:14:00,017
<i>Our board is taking note.</i>

169
00:14:00,018 --> 00:14:04,158
<i>Thought it was time you come to
North Carolina, discuss your future.</i>

170
00:14:04,159 --> 00:14:06,085
<i>What are we talking about here?</i>

171
00:14:06,086 --> 00:14:09,406
<i>Talking about you moving
up to Division One.</i>

172
00:14:09,407 --> 00:14:10,962
<i>Does Coach Hill know you doing this?</i>

173
00:14:10,963 --> 00:14:12,128
<i>He's retiring.</i>

174
00:14:12,129 --> 00:14:14,443
<i>He told me to contact you.</i>

175
00:14:14,444 --> 00:14:18,375
<i>Said the school needs one
of their own to come take the reins.</i>

176
00:14:18,376 --> 00:14:22,205
<i>What can I say?
Hell, yes, I'm interested.</i>

177
00:16:37,581 --> 00:16:40,032
<i>-What's going on?
-I don't know. It wasn't me.</i>

178
00:16:40,033 --> 00:16:44,049
<i>-Dad!
-Hannah! What is it?</i>

179
00:16:44,050 --> 00:16:45,468
<i>It was on my face! Get it off!</i>

180
00:16:45,468 --> 00:16:48,061
<i>-What are you talking about?
-It's under the covers!</i>

181
00:16:53,007 --> 00:16:55,082
<i>Dad!</i>

182
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:58,273
<i>-You did that on my bed.
-You told me to kill it.</i>

183
00:16:58,274 --> 00:17:00,240
<i>I told you to get it out.</i>

184
00:17:00,241 --> 00:17:02,206
<i>God, Dad.</i>

185
00:17:04,486 --> 00:17:06,294
<i>She told me to kill it.</i>

186
00:17:09,865 --> 00:17:11,552
<i>It's a moth!</i>

187
00:17:19,573 --> 00:17:23,508
<i>Make some noise for the
most dazzling divas of dance...</i>

188
00:17:23,509 --> 00:17:25,798
<i>...who always bring it fierce...</i>

189
00:17:25,799 --> 00:17:28,611
<i>...the Silver stars!</i>

190
00:17:28,612 --> 00:17:29,573
<i>Make me a home,
on my own, better make that bedrock</i>

191
00:17:36,010 --> 00:17:38,338
<i>Hey, are you okay?</i>

192
00:17:39,130 --> 00:17:41,495
<i>-I feel funny.
-What?</i>

193
00:17:41,496 --> 00:17:44,363
<i>-I feel funny.
-What do you mean?</i>

194
00:17:47,119 --> 00:17:48,871
<i>I don't feel like me.</i>

195
00:17:48,872 --> 00:17:51,736
<i>I know this stuff
with Mom and Dad sucks...</i>

196
00:17:51,737 --> 00:17:55,575
<i>...but we're just the kids,
and they're the adults...</i>

197
00:17:55,576 --> 00:17:58,716
<i>...and we have to go
along with their mistakes.</i>

198
00:17:58,717 --> 00:18:02,757
<i>But you'll feel better if
you just stopped giving a shit.</i>

199
00:18:15,586 --> 00:18:19,616
<i>Hi! Hey! Oh...</i>

200
00:18:19,617 --> 00:18:20,868
<i>Oh, hi, Mommy.</i>

201
00:18:20,869 --> 00:18:22,834
<i>-I missed you guys.
-I missed you too.</i>

202
00:18:22,835 --> 00:18:24,008
<i>How was the weekend?</i>

203
00:18:24,009 --> 00:18:26,826
<i>It was good. We had pizza.</i>

204
00:18:26,827 --> 00:18:30,178
<i>Wow, yes,
the new house has a pizza tree.</i>

205
00:18:30,179 --> 00:18:32,854
<i>-Is Jen's mom coming?
-Oh, yeah.</i>

206
00:18:32,855 --> 00:18:35,053
<i>Your outfit is on your bed...</i>

207
00:18:35,054 --> 00:18:37,660
<i>...and take one of your
allergy pills just in case.</i>

208
00:18:37,661 --> 00:18:40,594
<i>If one of your players had food allergies...</i>

209
00:18:40,595 --> 00:18:44,358
<i>...you'd write the cafeteria
ladies with menu demands.</i>

210
00:18:44,359 --> 00:18:45,454
<i>Cut me some slack.</i>

211
00:18:49,082 --> 00:18:50,214
<i>I was going get the boxes.</i>

212
00:18:50,215 --> 00:18:52,450
<i>-Okay.
-Okay.</i>

213
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:01,441
<i>What's with this guy?
Is he moving in or what?</i>

214
00:19:01,442 --> 00:19:05,040
<i>No. No, we're just dating.</i>

215
00:19:05,041 --> 00:19:06,168
<i>You're just dating?</i>

216
00:19:06,169 --> 00:19:09,474
<i>He's awfully comfortable
in the kitchen.</i>

217
00:19:09,475 --> 00:19:10,815
<i>Back off, Clyde.</i>

218
00:19:10,815 --> 00:19:14,496
<i>-In his antiseptic socks.
-At least he's present.</i>

219
00:19:14,497 --> 00:19:15,798
<i>Excuse me?</i>

